        <div >
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" class="f14" align="center">
                <tr>
                    <td colspan="2" align="center" >
                        <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" class="f14" align="center">
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                     <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" class="f14" align="center">
                                        <tr><td  align="left"> <h2> Lead Time validation</h2><br>  </td></tr>
                                        <tr> <td  align="center"><hr style="border-style: solid; border-color: red;"/> </td> </tr>
                                        <tr><td align="left"><br>There is a system based validation for lead time. System will not allow user to approve a request in case lead time is not met. Approver can either change the dates to match the lead time or escalate the request as business exigency.  In case of business exigency approval, old dates need not require to change.</td></tr>
                                        <tr><td align="left"><b> Remarks:</b></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td align="left">1>	Level 1 Approver has to approve the request within specified hours of receiving it, else the same will be escalated to Level 2 Approver.</td></tr>
                                        <tr><td align="left">2>	Level 2 Approver has to approve the request within specified hours of receiving it, else the same will be escalated as Business Exigency.</td></tr>
                                        <tr><td align="left">3>	In case of lead time not met the initiator can change the date and approve the request </td></tr>
                                        <tr><td align="left">4>	Send the request for business exigency in case the date needs to be same i.e. not fulfilling the lead time requirement</td></tr>
                                    </table>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr><td style="height: 15px;" colspan="2"></td></tr>
                        </table>
                    </td>
                </tr>
